text: Rolf Hellem (26 December 1923 - 6 June 2021) was a Norwegian politician. He was a member of the Labour Party. Hellem was born in Sør-Frøya, Norway. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Nordland in 1965. Hellem left office in 1981.
